comments: Murray (DEN) disengages from Dort's (OKC) resting hands on is body and establishes himself in Holmgren's (OKC) path as marginal contact occurs when the two come together during the screen.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Porter Jr. (DEN). Any follow-through contact as both players pursue the loose ball is deemed incidental.
Williams (OKC) briefly grasps and immediately releases Porter Jr.'s (DEN) arm that is extended toward his path as marginal contact occurs at the start of the drive.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) brings his hand toward Murray's (DEN) path and marginal contact occurs at the start of Murray's drive.
After the steal attempt, Holmgren (OKC) briefly rests his hand on Jokic's (DEN) body and immediately removes it as marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Jokic (DEN) goes to, not through, Holmgren's (OKC) space and marginal contact occurs as the two come together in the post.
Braun (DEN) avoids initiating any illegal contact with Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) during his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Murray (DEN) stops his forward momentum and slightly extends his forearm to release from the marginal contact with Dort (OKC) at the end of the drive.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) legally contests Murray's (DEN) jump shot attempt. Murray slightly extends his right leg out as he fades away to initiate any marginal contact with Gilgeous-Alexander.
Dort (OKC) and Jokic (DEN) mutually engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs before Dort sets the screen.
Gordon (DEN) brushes Williams' (OKC) right arm with his left hand and the contact is marginal.
Jokic (DEN) establishes himself in Dort's (OKC) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Holmgren (OKC) legally contests Jokic's (DEN) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
During the rebound, Watson (DEN) jumps alongside Joe (OKC) and makes contact with the ball to dislodge it. Any contact with Joe's arm that occurs simultaneous to the ball contact is deemed marginal.
Watson (DEN) maintains a legal guarding position and incidental contact occurs as he defends Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) at the end of the drive.
Watson (DEN) legally contests Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) jump shot attempt. Gilgeous-Alexander's own feet get briefly tangled as he returns to the ground, which causes him to lose his balance.
Dort (OKC) and Joe (OKC) make clean contact with the ball to deflect the inbound pass away from Gordon (DEN) and Murray (DEN).
Gordon (DEN) establishes himself in Dort's (OKC) path and absorbs the marginal contact during the screen.
